Sharing another post natal physio session I had at @thestretchclinic - 9 months post partum, I definitely have very different aches and pains when compared to the time I came for my first session 3 months post partum.

As I’m still breastfeeding, I wake up between 3-5 times in a night to breastfeed and also try and breastfeed during the day in all sorts of positions (you Mamas know what I’m talking about!) hence the most pressing aches I have is my upper and lower back pain, followed by aching arms (from having to carry Raisa a lot (not complaining!) and she grows so fast!) and hip pain. @jasmynpang definitely had my back (literally!) and walked me through all the corrections she made gently and gradually.

Highlight of the session for me was the back cracking twisting adjustment for sure! That needed to happen, and the pressure relief I had following that felt so good!

If you’d like to try a physio session out, use code FARA35 for RM35 off your first trial session. Also valid for post natal and sports massages! Thank me later!
